 * Applies smooth scrolling in every scrollable element when mouse wheel scroll occurs;
 * applies smooth scrolling in editor view when large jumps occur (e.g. when the cursor is moved by pressing PageUp or PageDown);
 * should fix #4606.

Considering that scrolling is 100% handled in JS, it would also be nice to make this feature configurable trough workspace/user settings, using for example `ui.mouseWheelSmoothScroll: true`, `ui.mouseWheelSmoothScrollDuration: 100`, `editor.smoothJumpScroll: true`, `editor.smoothJumpScrollDuration: 125`, or something similar. But I don't really know if and how the workspace configuration can be retrieved from [here](https://github.com/JD342/vscode/blob/7ec1ec3c4332ab21e02ed3fd582fbe64c65e9bbd/src/vs/base/browser/ui/scrollbar/scrollableElement.ts#L260) (or [here](https://github.com/JD342/vscode/blob/7ec1ec3c4332ab21e02ed3fd582fbe64c65e9bbd/src/vs/base/browser/ui/scrollbar/scrollableElement.ts#L417)) and [here](https://github.com/JD342/vscode/blob/7ec1ec3c4332ab21e02ed3fd582fbe64c65e9bbd/src/vs/editor/common/viewLayout/viewLayout.ts#L245).
